olor: #ccc;">woof paper</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Af=
ter we finished minting 1 quadrillion tokens, we put half into Uniswap and =
threw away the keys. Then, the remaining 50% was =E2=80=9Cburned=E2=80=9D t=
o Vitalik Buterin=E2=80=99s wallet, which was the start of our Army.</p></b=
lockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A footnote adds:</p><blockquote><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Please note that the Shib in VB=E2=80=99s wallet, =
at the time of this writing, was his #1 HIGHEST valued token, even exceedin=
g the value of the Ethereum there. This is an incredible accomplishment, an=
d we are just getting started.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
>As I understand it, inventors of altcoins sometimes =E2=80=9Cburn=E2=80=9D=
 a chunk of those coins to Buterin as a=C2=A0sort of publicity play. You ge=
t to say that Vitalik Buterin owns some of your coin. You get to inflate th=
e =E2=80=9Cmarket cap=E2=80=9D of your coin: Market cap is the trading pric=
e times the amount outstanding, and if you put trillions of coins in the ha=
nds of someone who won=E2=80=99t sell or spend them, you can inflate the mu=
ltiplier and achieve a huge market cap without much trading. And it is assu=
med by altcoin developers that Buterin=C2=A0<em>won=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>sel=
l the altcoins that get =E2=80=9Cburned=E2=80=9D to him, because that would=
 undermine his status as a pure-hearted evangelist for Ethereum, and becaus=
e he just seems to be too busy to spend any money.</p><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">I am sure that Buterin finds it a bit annoying to receive billions =
of dollars=E2=80=99=C2=A0worth of random altcoins? A few conclusions:</p><o=
l style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I cannot believe that I typed that sen=
tence; imagine being a person who is annoyed=C2=A0to wake up and find yours=
elf a billion dollars richer. Cryptocurrency economics are so weird.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Feel free to burn half of your billion=
-dollar altcoins to me instead I guess?=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">Buterin=E2=80=99s way of getting around this problem =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0<em>donating=C2=A0</em>the random altcoins to a worthy cause, and let=
ting the charity sell them =E2=80=94=C2=A0is pretty neat.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">That said, it doesn=E2=80=99t exactly solve the un=
derlying problem (the problem of people inventing random altcoins and sendi=
ng him a bunch), because this donation seems to have been free good publici=
ty for Shiba Inu, even if it did push down the price. Shiba Inu coin is som=
ehow providing hundreds of millions of dollars of Covid relief in India; se=
